        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41755",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "You can add routes anywhere before routing. However, since you're using zend_app, obviously you can just use the Router Resource Plugin: http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.application.available-resources.html rendering an _initRouter() method useless.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-27T07:34:21.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-27T07:34:21.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41756",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=harking",
                        "name": "harking",
                        "displayName": "George Montana Harkin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "That's fine, but there needs to be a blurb in http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.controller.router.html that discusses what you've just said. \r\n\r\nIs initRouter deprecated? If so there should be some documentation about this.\r\n\r\nThis should be open until the documentation linked above is updated.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=harking",
                        "name": "harking",
                        "displayName": "George Montana Harkin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-27T07:50:59.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-27T07:50:59.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41757",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": ">> That's fine, but there needs to be a blurb in http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.controller.router.html that discusses what you've just said.\r\n\r\nWhy does it need to be there? As said; you can configure the router at any place before the router gets called. However, if you want to do it using Zend_Application, you need to see the documentation on Zend_App.\r\n\r\n>> Is initRouter deprecated? If so there should be some documentation about this.\r\n\r\nI did _not_ say it is deprecated. All I said is that since there's a Resource Plugin shipped with ZF that does the configuring of the router for you, there's no sense in having an initRouter() method in your bootstrap.\r\n\r\n>> This should be open until the documentation linked above is updated.\r\n\r\nThat assumes the documentation will be updated according to this issue.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-27T07:58:24.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-27T07:58:24.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41758",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=harking",
                        "name": "harking",
                        "displayName": "George Montana Harkin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": ">> Why does it need to be there? As said; you can configure the router at any place before the router gets called. However, if you want to do it using Zend_Application, you need to see the documentation on Zend_App.\r\n\r\nIt needs to be there so new ZF developers don't waste time and can configure the router without searching unofficial sources for 10 minutes.  Just a link to the Zend_Application section would be enough to prevent this.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=harking",
                        "name": "harking",
                        "displayName": "George Montana Harkin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-27T08:06:35.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-27T08:06:35.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41759",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "A new developer will supposedly follow the quickstart guide http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/learning.quickstart.intro.html . ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-27T08:11:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-27T08:11:00.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41760",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=harking",
                        "name": "harking",
                        "displayName": "George Montana Harkin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": ">> A new developer will supposedly follow the quickstart guide http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/learning.quickstart.intro.html . \r\n\r\nPlease help me out, being a new developer to ZF, as I had already run through the quick start guide you linked. \r\n\r\nWhere does it mention routes and where they should live?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=harking",
                        "name": "harking",
                        "displayName": "George Montana Harkin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-27T08:16:58.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-27T08:16:58.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41761",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "That's a good question ;)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-27T08:23:03.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-27T08:23:03.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50801",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I agree with Dolf on this one:  The quickstart isn't meant to enumerate everything you can do with Zend Framework, just provide the basic introduction on how to get a basic application up and running.  The question is, where does one draw the line?  configuring routes? sessions? cache? Lucene search?  As it's meant to provide the most basic of introductions, it's best that we keep it simple, and any developers who want to do more will undoubtedly start consulting the manual section for each module they want to know more about. \r\n\r\nThat, and IMO the quick-start will become less and less relevant at this late stage in ZFv1's lifecycle as most people looking to pick up ZF from scratch will choose ZF2 over ZF1. \r\n\r\nRecommend closing as \"Won't Fix\"",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-05-29T12:28:43.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-05-29T12:28:43.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
